<subSubSection id="79DA6524362CFC0EC482DC3AFCAAB358" pageId="21" pageNumber="386" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="317F36AF362CFC0EC482DC3AFCAAB358" blockId="21.[178,1085,261,342]" pageId="21" pageNumber="386">
The nominate subgenus previously comprised 34 species in the Palaearctic region (
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E362CFC0EC489DC1DFEE0B335" author="ASSING V" box="[185,335,290,312]" pageId="21" pageNumber="386" pagination="277 - 331" refId="ref19827" refString="ASSING V. (2006 a): On some species of Oxypoda MANNERHEIM from Turkey and adjacent regions (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 38 (1): 277 - 331." type="journal article" year="2006">ASSING 2006a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E362CFC0EC56BDC1DFE33B335" author="ASSING V" box="[347,412,290,312]" pageId="21" pageNumber="386" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref19906" refString="ASSING V. (2007 a): New species and additional records of Staphylinidae from Turkey V (Coleoptera). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde Serie A (Biologie) 700: 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">2007a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E362CFC0EC599DC1CFDB2B335" author="PACE R" box="[425,541,290,312]" pageId="21" pageNumber="386" pagination="189 - 204" refId="ref20838" refString="PACE R. (2002): Aleocharinae aus Kasachstan (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Veroffentlichungen Naturkundemuseum Erfurt 21: 189 - 204." type="journal article" year="2002">PACE 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E362CFC0EC619DC1DFD64B335" author="SMETANA A" box="[553,715,290,312]" pageId="21" pageNumber="386" pagination="353 - 494" refId="ref21053" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamily Aleocharinae, pp. 353 - 494. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea-Histeroidea- Staphylinoidea. Stenstrup: Apollo Books, 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Some of them are associated with nests and burrows of small mammals (marmot, mole, etc.).
</paragraph>
